  "body": "_If you are reporting a bug, please include reproduction steps._\r\n\r\nAt step [https://hardhat.org/getting-started/#testing-your-contracts](https://hardhat.org/getting-started/#testing-your-contracts), the test failed with this error message\r\n```bash\r\nGreeter\r\n    1) Should return the new greeting once it's changed\r\n\r\n  0 passing (11ms)\r\n  1 failing\r\n\r\n  1) Greeter\r\n       Should return the new greeting once it's changed:\r\n     *ReferenceError: ethers is not defined*\r\n      *at Context.<anonymous> (test/sample-test.js:5:21)*\r\n      at processImmediate (internal/timers.js:456:21)\r\n\r\n``` \r\nI understood that `ethers` is added automatically by hardhat?\r\n\r\nMy installed versions\r\n```bash\r\n+ chai@4.3.4\r\n+ ethers@5.4.1\r\n+ ethereum-waffle@3.4.0\r\n+ @nomiclabs/hardhat-waffle@2.0.1\r\n+ @nomiclabs/hardhat-ethers@2.0.2\r\n\r\n```",
