    "body": "Awesome tutorial. I've also finished deploying the smart contract on the local node. Very good tuto.\r\n\r\nMaybe one suggestion: remove the [note about plug-ins](https://hardhat.org/getting-started/#running-tasks) off the mainstream logic, for example into an annex. Focus the beginner on the main actions. Specially because at this moment of the tuto, the beginner is still expecting only the most important topics.\r\n```bash\r\nkvutien@VTKT5 hardhat-trial % npx hardhat run scripts/sample-script.js --network localhost\r\nweb3_clientVersion (2)\r\neth_chainId\r\neth_accounts\r\neth_blockNumber\r\neth_chainId (2)\r\neth_estimateGas\r\neth_gasPrice\r\neth_sendTransaction\r\n  Contract deployment: Greeter\r\n  Contract address:    0x5fbdb2315678afecb367f032d93f642f64180aa3\r\n  Transaction:         0x8a13cd0caabb1b116b69213ae6e2a96a36dcb1c48982a848e809e91603b307a2\r\n  From:                0xf39fd6e51aad88f6f4ce6ab8827279cfffb92266\r\n  Value:               0 ETH\r\n  Gas used:            488014 of 488014\r\n  Block #1:            0x7990c257fc619c5c66c25c964000bd5141fcc2b29cbb6c8f42540fe967963d6b\r\n\r\n  console.log:\r\n    Deploying a Greeter with greeting: Hello, Hardhat!\r\n\r\neth_chainId\r\neth_getTransactionByHash\r\neth_chainId\r\neth_getTransactionReceipt\r\nGreeter deployed to: 0x5FbDB2315678afecb367f032d93F642f64180aa3\r\n```",
